title: Remove Duplicates from Sorted List
content: Given the head of a sorted linked list, delete all duplicates such that each element appears only once. Return the linked list sorted as well.   Example 1: Input: head = [1,1,2] Output: [1,2] Example 2: Input: head = [1,1,2,3,3] Output: [1,2,3]   Constraints: The number of nodes in the list is in the range [0, 300]. -100 <= Node.val <= 100 The list is guaranteed to be sorted in ascending order.
